# Webex AI Agent Studio - Design System Rules

## Overview

This document defines the design system for the Webex AI Agent Studio prototype. Use these guidelines when integrating Figma designs or making UI changes.

---

## 1. Token Definitions

### Color Tokens

Design tokens are defined as CSS custom properties in `:root`:

```css
:root {
  /* Backgrounds */
  --bg-primary: #f5f7fa;      /* Main background */
  --bg-secondary: #ffffff;    /* Card/surface background */
  --bg-sidebar: #1a1a2e;      /* Dark sidebar background */

  /* Text Colors */
  --text-primary: #1a1a2e;    /* Primary text */
  --text-secondary: #64748b;  /* Secondary/muted text */
  --text-muted: #94a3b8;      /* Disabled/hint text */

  /* UI Colors */
  --border-color: #e2e8f0;    /* Borders and dividers */
  --accent-color: #0066cc;    /* Primary action color (Webex blue) */
  --accent-hover: #0052a3;    /* Hover state for accent */

  /* Semantic Colors */
  --success-color: #10b981;   /* Success states */
  --warning-color: #f59e0b;   /* Warning states */
  --danger-color: #ef4444;    /* Error/danger states */
}
```

### Gradient Tokens

Used for agent avatars and decorative elements:

```css
/* Primary gradient (purple) */
background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);

/* Success gradient (green) */
